    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Scouts' Successful Ban on Gays Is Followed by Loss in Support'' (front page, Aug. 29): In addition to discriminating against gays, the Boy Scouts bar as members and leaders those who won't publicly declare their personal belief in God. That religious test is offensive to American ideals and is itself sufficient reason for individuals, companies and governments to deny material support to the Scouts.</p>
        <p>NORRIS HOYT  Norwich, Vt., Aug. 29, 2000</p>
      </block>
